parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stops moving while the engine is still running
the transmission slips when shifting
the transmission fails to engage
difficulty shifting gears
loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic ignition system can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the ignition system fails to function
the vehicle experiences intermittent starting issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire in the engine compartment, leading to a risk of injury or property damage.
symptoms: A fire breaks out in the engine compartment
electrical short circuits
burning of wires and hoses
engine stalling or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The ABS system light illuminates on the dashboard
the brake light illuminates on the dashboard
brake fluid leaks from the system
the vehicle's brakes fail to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the air conditioner's electrical system can cause the air conditioner to remain on even when the vehicle is turned off, leading to battery drain and potentially causing a fire hazard. Additionally, the intermittent failure of the air conditioner can cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The air conditioner does not turn off when the vehicle is turned off
the air conditioner cuts off intermittently
the air conditioner only blows on low
the air conditioner fails to operate altogether
the air conditioner is affected by the use of other electrical accessories such as the blinker or wipers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window motor can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and in some cases, may obstruct the driver's view, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windows do not roll up or down
windows roll up or down slowly
windows make a grinding or screeching noise when operating
windows stop working suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear view mirror mounting can cause the mirror to fall off the windshield, obstructing the driver's rear view and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear view mirror falls off the windshield
the rear view mirror is loose or unstable
the rear view mirror is difficult to adjust or stays in place.
